  "text": "Turn the volume all the way up! Round of 16, 7 July 2026 — and Argentina produced a stunning comeback, turning a two-goal deficit into a stoppage-time victory. The reigning champions stared elimination in the face, two goals down and with their talisman's penalty already saved.\n\n46' — Omar Ibrahim buried it, 0–1! 67' — Zico lashed it home, 0–2! 79' — Cristian Romero made no mistake, 1–2! 84' — Lionel Messi found the net, 2–2! 94' — Enzo Fernández smashed it in, 3–2!\n\nOmar Ibrahim and Zico had Egypt dreaming at 2-0, and Lionel Messi even saw a penalty saved by an inspired Mohamed Shobeir. Then the tie turned on its head: Cristian Romero powered in a header from Messi's cross, before Messi himself pounced on a loose ball for his 21st career World Cup goal. In the second minute of stoppage time, Enzo Fernández arrived with a lung-busting run to head Lautaro Martínez's cross into the top corner. Champions find a way, and Argentina — through sheer force of Messi's will — found one when it mattered most.\n\nYou could feel the tension crackle around the ground with every attack.\n\nThis is knockout football at its rawest — win, or fly home.\n\nFULL-TIME: Argentina 3–2 Egypt! Argentina march on, Egypt head home heartbroken — and here's the beautiful part: every goal, every minute you just heard is locked on-chain and verified by TxLINE. No hot air, no guesswork, just receipts. What. A. Game!",
